WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:03.458
Hi, I'm Pastor Tori Brooks and welcome to Faith Christian Church.

00:03.478 --> 00:04.700
So glad you could join us today.

00:05.221 --> 00:09.166
For the next 30 minutes, we're going to be looking through God's Word and finding ways for it to apply to our lives today.

00:09.707 --> 00:11.129
Hope you enjoy this morning's service.

00:12.031 --> 00:12.772
Oh, praise the Lord.

00:13.773 --> 00:28.635
I want to finish talking to you this morning about definitions because I really feel like it's time to move on, but I wanted to talk about one more word that I think is very important, especially when it comes to daily Christian living.

00:29.176 --> 00:30.418
Because this word,

00:30.690 --> 00:42.123
has been misinterpreted many, many times in the past as a word that is defined by one's individual definition of it instead of God's definition of it.

00:43.484 --> 00:47.449
And I just want to take you through a couple of previous stories.

00:47.849 --> 00:59.282
We're going to walk a little bit through the Old Testament and then talk about Jesus and come through the New Testament because I want to give you a good scope of God's vision of what this word should mean

00:59.554 --> 01:04.941
in our daily Christian living and of course the word I want to talk about this morning is the word sacrifice.

01:06.723 --> 01:23.826
Now one of the key beginning stories and all stories have a beginning obviously but when we talk about beginnings we always in Bible refer to the book of Genesis and there's no greater picture of sacrifice in the book of Genesis than Abraham and Isaac in Genesis chapter 22

01:23.970 --> 01:33.265
In this story we find that God tells Abraham that he wants Abraham to sacrifice his son Isaac, his only son Isaac.

01:33.506 --> 01:39.976
Now we know that he had another son Ishmael before, but God did not refer to Ishmael as being the promised child.

01:40.197 --> 01:47.328
I don't know if you remember this or not, but God made a promise to Abraham and Sarah that they were going to have a child and through that child they were going to be the father of many nations.

01:47.368 --> 01:48.370
Now the problem

01:48.482 --> 01:53.008
with this is that at the time God promised Abraham and Sarah, they were going to have a child.

01:53.148 --> 01:56.673
Abraham and Sarah were, well, old.

01:58.856 --> 02:01.160
Not putting anything on older people, but they were old.

02:01.981 --> 02:09.531
Here they were in their upper 90s and they're beyond the age of giving birth to children.

02:09.551 --> 02:11.634
And to be honest, I don't know if

02:11.842 --> 02:15.246
People who are in their 90s would even want to care for a baby anyway.

02:15.786 --> 02:20.632
I tell Bethany, I said, I'm, you know, here I am 36 years old and I'm glad all the children are here.

02:21.052 --> 02:25.036
You know, I don't know what I'd do with a little bitty baby, but it'd probably drive me crazy.

02:25.056 --> 02:33.305
But the idea that God was going to give to a child was in the natural impossible, but how many, you know, God is a supernatural God.

02:34.386 --> 02:36.048
He doesn't do things just in the natural.

02:36.068 --> 02:37.650
He does things supernaturally.

02:38.050 --> 02:49.247
And all through our Bible studies of Genesis and even Exodus, I have to remind us constantly that it may seem impossible to us because we understand laws and physics and things like that.

02:49.628 --> 02:51.230
But God is beyond any of that.

02:51.510 --> 02:55.657
He operates outside time and physics and the laws.

02:55.937 --> 02:57.079
He invented the laws of nature.

02:57.119 --> 03:01.285
So as the creator of those laws, he's also over those laws.

03:01.365 --> 03:04.370
And he doesn't have to follow the things that we think he should.

03:04.642 --> 03:11.794
And so God gave Abraham and Sarah this beautiful boy Isaac who was born in their old age.

03:12.335 --> 03:18.024
And here he is a young boy and God says to Abraham, now take this wonderful child I've given you and kill him.

03:20.428 --> 03:24.114
Now anybody in their right mind would have obviously said you've got to be crazy.

03:24.834 --> 03:27.839
This is all of our hopes and dreams have been put into this one child.

03:27.979 --> 03:35.791
All of the fulfillment of God's promises seem to be placed in this one single child and yet here God says I want you to kill him.

03:35.811 --> 03:39.857
Now what God was doing with Abraham was not necessarily wanting him to kill the child.

03:40.198 --> 03:43.122
He was testing Abraham's obedience.

03:43.142 --> 03:49.272
I want you to understand that the words obedience and sacrifice were made to go hand in hand when it comes to the Bible.

03:50.053 --> 03:53.138
When God asked for a sacrifice, he always intended it

03:53.314 --> 03:54.375
to be done.

03:54.656 --> 03:59.201
There was never this, and any time it wasn't done, it was considered disobedience to God.

03:59.521 --> 04:00.242
Well, we know the story.

04:00.322 --> 04:12.157
Abraham goes up to the mountain and he ties him down to the altar, and then right before he stabs his son Isaac to kill him, an angel appears and says, don't kill him.

04:13.018 --> 04:13.518
Don't do it.

04:13.598 --> 04:15.220
You fulfilled what God wanted to see.

04:15.681 --> 04:17.803
In fact, God's provided, look over here.

04:17.844 --> 04:23.250
God's provided something for the sacrifice, and there was a ram stuck in the thicket, and it must have been a really big thicket.

04:23.394 --> 04:31.644
to get stuck, because Rams are usually powerful animals, but he got stuck, and they both came down off the mountain.

04:32.144 --> 04:44.178
It was the obedience to this idea of sacrifice that God rewarded Abraham for, and in the Bible later on in the New Testament, God honors Abraham for being willing to sacrifice his son Isaac.

04:45.240 --> 04:50.706
By the time we come to Moses in Exodus 23, sacrifice becomes almost mandatory.

04:50.818 --> 04:53.821
for the feast and for other things involving the law.

04:54.281 --> 04:57.044
Now the idea of sacrificing the law was very simple.

04:57.524 --> 05:02.149
When you sin, you must pay for your sins.

05:02.169 --> 05:08.335
I think this concept almost lost today on younger people because they get away with almost everything.

05:08.695 --> 05:14.160
You know, I often have been criticized because I'll tell my kids on a car trip.

05:14.521 --> 05:17.764
If you don't stop it, I'm turning this car around.

05:18.905 --> 05:20.146
Well, if you know me,

05:20.994 --> 05:23.438
You know, I'm not going to turn the car around.

05:23.458 --> 05:26.002
I'm going to McDonald's.

05:26.022 --> 05:34.296
You know, I'm going, you know, but I want them to believe that there's inside of me a desire to turn the car around and go home and eat a sandwich.

05:35.858 --> 05:37.661
Nasty peanut butter and jelly.

05:38.122 --> 05:40.145
But I want them to behave.

05:40.165 --> 05:43.150
And if they behave, we will continue on to victory.

05:43.450 --> 05:48.178
But if not, we will, the thought of being, and you know what, a lot of times we just go on and it doesn't matter.

05:49.314 --> 05:55.162
And the kids think, hey, if we were loud the last time and he turned the car around, we can be loud the second time.

05:56.785 --> 06:01.411
We were on a trip one time and, you know, it was like, we had planned this trip for months.

06:01.552 --> 06:04.997
We're going to the beach and told the kids, we were 30 miles from the beach.

06:05.738 --> 06:08.442
Said, if you don't stop it, we're turning the car around.

06:08.522 --> 06:10.244
And I looked at my wife and said, we can't do that.

06:11.726 --> 06:14.290
You know how much time and effort and energy we just spent.

06:14.498 --> 06:22.470
$55 on brand new boogie boards, and I've even put aside my fair sharks for the day.

06:22.490 --> 06:32.865
I said, I've put on the mind of Christ, cast out all fear, and I'm ready to go in the ocean, even though there could be a shark, I'm going.

06:34.768 --> 06:44.082
If we're gonna tell the kids they're gonna have to pay for some wrong they do, at least let's make it something that we can do that we're going to do, and not something that we're just pretending we might do.

06:45.858 --> 06:48.521
Well, the parchment for sin was always severe.

06:48.581 --> 06:54.228
In fact, God created a system of sacrifice where that if you sinned, you were to take an animal.

06:58.133 --> 07:01.618
And with one hand, you were to place your hand on the animal's head.

07:04.121 --> 07:07.185
And in symbolism, pass your sin onto the animal.

07:08.246 --> 07:11.570
And with the other hand, you were to take the ceremonial knife and to kill that animal.

07:13.602 --> 07:23.154
Now the horror of this exercise was to make people feel bad for having to kill the animal and not do it anymore.

07:26.599 --> 07:31.205
Because you would think after a while, you know, you get attached to these animals.

07:31.225 --> 07:34.910
These are animals you either bought or you raised yourself.

07:35.230 --> 07:41.458
And sometimes you would think that people would be onto this as something that would be, I don't want to ever do that again.

07:43.074 --> 07:48.121
And yet, sacrificial system became something that was just done all the time.

07:50.725 --> 07:59.097
In fact, it became so, so, so just ordinary and common that it would just happen all the time.

07:59.117 --> 08:03.444
There was never a time that the authors didn't stop flowing with blood because the people sinned.

08:04.145 --> 08:10.674
In fact, later on, we'll find out that people were doing it, were raising animals just so they would have something to sacrifice.

08:12.546 --> 08:14.210
just so that they would have something in the time.

08:15.132 --> 08:17.537
But sacrifice wasn't all that God demanded.

08:17.798 --> 08:20.023
Sometimes God wanted just obedience.

08:21.085 --> 08:24.754
Because sometimes in the obedience made a sacrifice on our own part.

08:25.215 --> 08:28.342
There was a story in 1 Samuel, chapter 15 about Saul.

08:28.783 --> 08:31.890
Saul was not the best king in the world, but he was Israel's first king.

08:32.674 --> 08:39.685
And Saul had in mind to make himself a man higher stature than when he was told by God to go in.

08:39.745 --> 08:43.691
I want you to kill every man, woman, and child, every living creature.

08:43.711 --> 08:46.334
I want you to wipe in and decimate the whole place.

08:47.316 --> 08:49.599
And Saul didn't do it.

08:51.883 --> 08:56.690
In fact, Saul wanting to make a name for himself decided he would take the king

08:56.866 --> 09:05.619
who was a man of higher stature, King Agag, and he would take King Agag and haul him through the streets of the city, showing everybody, look what I captured.

09:06.741 --> 09:23.186
And then he took all these animals, the Bible said they were the better animals or the good animals or the better animals, animals for sacrifice to take these animals and they were going to go in and have this glorious feast and mock the king.

09:26.306 --> 09:35.556
When the prophet came through, knowing the mind of God, the prophet came, Samuel came in and said, listen, why do I keep hearing all of these sheep and animals?

09:36.297 --> 09:37.679
Weren't you supposed to kill everything?

09:37.719 --> 09:40.202
He said, well, I wanted to honor God.

09:42.785 --> 09:45.307
I wanted, all this is for God.

09:45.367 --> 09:54.738
I just wanted to show God, well, all that wasn't for God because if he would done it for God, he would have done exactly what God told him to do.

09:55.778 --> 10:03.226
What he did was he wanted everybody to see him walking in triumphant, walking in victorious and leading the king around by a rope on his neck.

10:06.830 --> 10:10.574
Samuel tells us some words that should resonate in our minds.

10:10.654 --> 10:17.301
And yet sometimes it is the words we put back all the time in the church of Samuel.

10:17.321 --> 10:22.066
Samuel says, it's better to obey than the sacrifice.

10:25.602 --> 10:30.727
By the time Isaiah, the prophet comes around, Isaiah chapter one, God says, you know what?

10:31.227 --> 10:33.089
Sacrifices have become meaningless.

10:34.711 --> 10:39.575
Now, the law was set up so that sacrifices were supposed to mean something to you.

10:39.976 --> 10:51.066
You were supposed to feel the connection of what your sin does, the damage your sin causes, the problems and conflicts, the cost of sin was supposed to cost you something.

10:51.086 --> 10:55.250
And yet, by the time Isaiah comes around, God says, you know what, I've had enough.

10:57.346 --> 10:58.908
Your sacrifices are worthless.

10:59.890 --> 11:01.612
Why were the sacrifices worthless?

11:01.632 --> 11:10.865
They were worthless because even though they did what was proper according to the law, the attitude of men's hearts never changed.

11:10.885 --> 11:12.928
Listen, the attitude of men's hearts never changed.

11:13.348 --> 11:17.875
The attitude was when you sacrifice, it's supposed to do something to you.

11:19.016 --> 11:23.282
It's supposed to remind you of the penalties and remind you of the cost.

11:27.586 --> 11:28.247
And yet they didn't.

11:30.872 --> 11:31.693
They just kept on.

11:33.356 --> 11:46.318
Even after the captivity in Babylon, the one thing they wanted to do was just rebuild the temple so they could keep on sacrificing.

11:49.363 --> 11:51.026
Luckily for us, Jesus came.

11:53.122 --> 12:00.933
And as much as I wanted to get into all the things Jesus did for us, the overall point is Jesus came and made the perfect sacrifice.

12:03.877 --> 12:10.426
And in making the perfect sacrifice, he did exactly what he needed so that we could have the perfect sacrifice to cover our sins.

12:12.349 --> 12:17.896
The problem though with the church was, and still seems to be the problem with the church's two things.

12:18.177 --> 12:22.162
One, the sacrifice of Jesus for our sins

12:22.722 --> 12:27.690
When we know that he sacrificed his life for our sins, it's supposed to do something in us.

12:30.554 --> 12:40.109
Do you know that when I was first told the story of Jesus dying on the cross from my sins, I didn't grab the full picture of what that looked like.

12:40.890 --> 12:43.474
Being a child from the visual generation,

12:43.650 --> 12:49.918
And we believe everything we see on TV because it registers in our minds as being true and accurate.

12:50.619 --> 12:54.644
I never really caught it because it was just words on the page or words being spoken.

12:54.724 --> 13:03.074
And then movies come out like the Jesus film or the Passion of the Christ and suddenly the visualization of the sacrifice of Jesus.

13:04.095 --> 13:09.682
And yet you would think with all the visuals we have of Jesus' sacrifice, it would do something to us.

13:13.986 --> 13:29.686
you would think our lives would be forever changed, our consciences would be forever marked with the idea that this man came and shed his blood and died because I missed the mark because I sinned.

13:33.270 --> 13:35.593
In fact, it should stir us up to never sin again.

13:35.633 --> 13:42.962
There should be something inside of us that says, listen, knowing what Jesus did for me, I never want to sin again.

13:45.154 --> 13:51.463
And yet most people just keep on saying it.

13:51.483 --> 13:55.468
The problem with sacrifices, we don't really understand what it means to us.

13:57.992 --> 14:05.562
And I just want to talk just a little bit more today about what Jesus said, sacrifice is supposed to mean for us.

14:06.604 --> 14:14.034
He being the ultimate solution for the problem of sin also includes us in there,

14:14.114 --> 14:20.903
to follow after him, to sacrifice ourselves for what he wanted us to do.

14:21.945 --> 14:24.508
Again, sacrifice with obedience.

14:24.528 --> 14:28.914
This is what Jesus says in Matthew chapter 16, starting in verse number 24.

14:29.875 --> 14:36.945
Then Jesus said to his disciples, if anyone desires to come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

14:37.686 --> 14:43.634
For whoever desires to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life for my sake will find it.

14:44.226 --> 14:48.752
For what profit is it to a man if he games the whole world and loses his soul?

14:50.074 --> 14:52.197
Or what will a man give in exchange for his soul?

14:52.978 --> 15:04.994
For the Son of Man will come in the glory of his father and with his angels and then he will reward each one according to his works.

15:05.014 --> 15:08.799
I think one of the problems we have in the church today is understanding our word sacrifice.

15:08.839 --> 15:09.721
What does it mean to us?

15:11.122 --> 15:13.746
Because here's what sacrifice means to a lot of people.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.656
Sacrifice means this to a lot of people.

15:16.676 --> 15:23.983
I will give what I feel like giving when I feel like giving it and will deem it a sacrifice because I'm giving something.

15:26.565 --> 15:28.067
I can't tell you the number of times.

15:31.490 --> 15:43.922
I know I shouldn't say that, but I can't tell you the number of times people give that it's not necessary to give or they give out of feeling guilty instead of giving out of the abundance of their heart.

15:44.162 --> 15:45.504
giving because God asked them to.

15:46.466 --> 15:53.717
Can I tell you the one thing that has just sparked inside of my mind and I was praying, God, give me a phrase to help people understand this.

15:54.418 --> 15:55.400
And this is what he gave me.

15:55.540 --> 15:59.466
Sacrifice without obedience is wasteful.

16:03.433 --> 16:07.119
Listen, sacrifice without obedience is wasteful.

16:08.180 --> 16:11.826
When we claim that we're doing something and we're sacrificing,

16:12.066 --> 16:15.972
for God and God's never asked us to do that, then we're wasting our time.

16:17.394 --> 16:18.475
We're wasting our energy.

16:18.495 --> 16:21.520
We're wasting our resources and wasting our finances.

16:22.882 --> 16:27.148
Listen, part of what living for God is about is obedience.

16:27.569 --> 16:30.112
And yes, God does ask us to sacrifice ourselves.

16:30.453 --> 16:37.123
Listen, Jesus said, listen, if you wanna come after me, if you wanna be my disciple, if you wanna live this Christian life, you've got to deny yourself.

16:37.483 --> 16:39.346
And a lot of people aren't willing to sacrifice that.

16:39.426 --> 16:43.953
You know, most people when they're growing up, they have dreams and ambitions and goals.

16:44.294 --> 16:45.736
They have, I want to be this.

16:45.796 --> 16:46.397
I'll never forget.

16:46.798 --> 16:48.321
I had a whole list of things I wanted to be.

16:50.324 --> 16:51.766
Now, obviously you can't be all that list.

16:52.568 --> 16:53.810
Just not have time.

16:53.830 --> 16:55.532
Not going to be 969 years old.

16:55.833 --> 16:56.915
I won't, maybe 140.

16:56.975 --> 17:01.362
That's my goal, but you know, I'm not going to be able to be all these things that I want to be.

17:02.914 --> 17:10.702
But I began to realize something when I gave my heart and life to Jesus Christ, what I wanted and what he wanted could be two separate things.

17:12.063 --> 17:20.251
And I must be willing to say, if this is not what you want, God, let me sacrifice all this other stuff, put it away, put aside and follow after you in obedience.

17:21.392 --> 17:25.916
Now, let's say part of that is not something that Jesus told me to sacrifice.

17:25.957 --> 17:31.602
And I threw all that talent away because I felt like I just wanted, I wanted to do this.

17:32.898 --> 17:43.912
I could go through a whole lot of different things in my mind that I'm thinking of, but listen, whatever, but it's not just about sacrificing for sacrificing saying.

17:43.932 --> 17:48.598
It's about saying, Jesus, what do you want me to sacrifice?

17:48.618 --> 17:55.187
Now, most people aren't going to do that in life because we don't like the idea of going up to Jesus and going, hi, Jesus, good morning.

17:55.207 --> 17:56.949
What do you like me to sacrifice today?

17:58.972 --> 18:00.914
Because most of us feel like we don't have anything to begin with.

18:02.146 --> 18:05.431
And to give up more for Jesus would just be too much for us.

18:06.754 --> 18:11.201
And yet Jesus says this, what profits a man if he has everything he ever wants in life?

18:12.904 --> 18:14.807
He has every desire of his heart.

18:16.109 --> 18:18.773
He loses his soul because he didn't obey.

18:18.833 --> 18:24.262
There are countless times throughout the Bible where Jesus asked people to surrender of themselves.

18:24.522 --> 18:29.170
In fact, when Jesus makes this comment in Matthew 16, it is after the crowds have gone.

18:31.810 --> 18:39.179
He is going through a part where everybody was on the bandwagon and now everybody's off the bandwagon.

18:39.199 --> 18:40.341
So that's the thing with Jesus.

18:40.681 --> 18:42.704
You got to understand living for him.

18:42.764 --> 18:43.965
It's not an easy thing.

18:46.348 --> 18:49.933
Sacrificing yourself, denying yourself is not an easy thing.

18:52.316 --> 18:54.098
And that's why most people don't do it.

18:55.490 --> 19:08.789
They don't do it because they understand that to give themselves up to God, to surrender their lives to Jesus Christ, to sacrifice themselves means you give up everything that you want for everything that he wants.

19:10.271 --> 19:10.932
It's not easy.

19:12.534 --> 19:21.106
I can't tell you the number of people I know today that aren't in ministry because when Jesus asked them to make the sacrifice of their lives to commit,

19:21.218 --> 19:22.580
to following him with all their hearts.

19:22.600 --> 19:23.282
You know what they said?

19:23.662 --> 19:37.306
I would love to as long as I can keep this, as long as I can keep that, as long as I can keep my car or I can keep my house, as long as I can keep this job or I can keep this thing.

19:38.208 --> 19:41.614
And listen, I'm telling you, Jesus has called us to sacrificial living.

19:42.616 --> 19:46.162
Do you know the gospel should be considered to be a sacrificial gospel?

19:47.426 --> 19:52.995
Well, like Kevin said this morning in prayer, it's become a save all gospel, a help all gospel.

19:53.055 --> 19:54.557
Do this in your whole world.

19:54.577 --> 20:02.529
We'll turn into roses and without thorns, you know, and come high and all this wonderful stuff.

20:02.830 --> 20:10.281
And yet the Bible always talks about sacrifice, sacrifice, sacrifice.

20:10.301 --> 20:13.426
Real living in Jesus Christ is going to come with sacrifices.

20:14.306 --> 20:18.470
It's going to come with times when you have to deny yourself and give up something for him.

20:19.912 --> 20:25.037
For some of you, it may be God may say, I want you to sell this and give it to whatever.

20:25.758 --> 20:30.423
You know, I'll never tell you that God's going to tell you to sell everything you've got and give it to the church.

20:31.945 --> 20:35.188
That's not for me to say, but he may.

20:36.770 --> 20:40.594
He may say, I want you to give up what you're doing and follow after me.

20:43.682 --> 20:48.107
He may say, I want you to give up a Saturday and join the evangelism team.

20:49.388 --> 20:51.390
Do you not know God?

20:51.410 --> 20:53.112
That Saturdays are my day off.

20:54.974 --> 20:56.596
God says, I know everything about you.

20:57.657 --> 20:58.878
I know the hairs on your head.

20:59.980 --> 21:01.381
I know every tear you've ever cried.

21:01.902 --> 21:03.503
I know every pain you feel in your body.

21:04.244 --> 21:09.069
Of course I know you and I know your schedule.

21:09.089 --> 21:13.394
The problem is the church wants to sacrifice when it wants to sacrifice.

21:14.498 --> 21:20.043
and doesn't want to sacrifice when it needs to sacrifice.

21:20.063 --> 21:34.818
It's a shame how much has been wasted in the church because people gave the wrong thing at the wrong time out of their own desire to be noticed instead of their desire to serve and obey God.

21:34.838 --> 21:40.944
See, we don't get to pick and choose what we sacrifice to Him when He asks.

21:40.964 --> 21:43.506
I can imagine Abraham

21:44.130 --> 21:46.734
You're going to think bad to me, but don't just listen to me.

21:47.516 --> 21:51.522
I can imagine Abraham when God says, I want you to sacrifice your son.

21:55.249 --> 21:58.153
And I imagine the first son Abraham looked at was an Isaac.

22:01.198 --> 22:04.143
Let's be honest.

22:04.163 --> 22:06.708
Can I sacrifice one of the wives, you know?

22:07.349 --> 22:08.671
Can I sacrifice something else?

22:08.971 --> 22:10.514
Can I do something instead?

22:11.106 --> 22:11.847
Can I barter?

22:11.887 --> 22:12.487
But you know what?

22:12.788 --> 22:14.189
You can't barter with God.

22:15.290 --> 22:23.639
When God asks you to be obedient, when He asks you to sacrifice of yourself, He's not doing it because He's got Plan B and C on standby.

22:23.679 --> 22:25.281
He's doing it because He's relying on you.

22:28.124 --> 22:30.907
The great thing about God is God will always come through for His people.

22:30.927 --> 22:37.554
But the sad thing is, is that when we don't obey the curse that comes upon us.

22:41.282 --> 22:52.917
When Jesus gives the instructions on how to follow after him, I can imagine that all the glamour and glory of the feeding of the 5,000 just drained off their faces.

22:56.282 --> 23:00.968
And there was no more talk about tent revivals and newspaper articles.

23:03.251 --> 23:05.894
Jesus wasn't talking about parades with palm branches.

23:07.456 --> 23:08.658
He's talking about crosses.

23:09.794 --> 23:11.556
It was talking about ultimate sacrifices.

23:13.998 --> 23:19.504
And the reality is today it would be hard for some of you.

23:20.405 --> 23:27.272
If Jesus Christ came into this room today and said, I want you to sacrifice your life for me.

23:29.795 --> 23:31.436
I want you to go to this country.

23:31.456 --> 23:32.397
I want you to do this.

23:32.457 --> 23:33.358
I want you to do that.

23:34.820 --> 23:36.882
Would you give up everything to follow after me?

23:37.890 --> 23:42.755
Most of us would have to think twice because it's a hard thing.

23:45.058 --> 23:47.300
Don't ever think that living for Jesus is easy.

23:48.682 --> 23:51.405
Don't ever think that obeying God is going to be a piece of cake.

23:52.867 --> 23:58.153
But can I tell you that everyone who ever sacrificed for Jesus Christ was rewarded?

24:00.735 --> 24:01.416
Now listen to me.

24:02.077 --> 24:05.160
You say, well pastor, I don't see Peter rewarded.

24:06.262 --> 24:06.642
Dude,

24:07.170 --> 24:09.732
Man, he hung on a tree upside down and died.

24:10.894 --> 24:18.641
But I can tell you the moment his last breath left his body and he came to see Jesus face to face in heaven.

24:19.141 --> 24:20.222
It was all worth it.

24:22.445 --> 24:32.514
See, we have gotten in our minds that the reward of the church is on earth, that the reward of the church is how big a tenant you have or how much money you have in the bank.

24:32.955 --> 24:36.498
Do you know that Jesus never intended the reward of the church to be on earth?

24:38.050 --> 24:44.798
Jesus never intended the reward of the individual Christian to have their name on papers or to sell multi-million dollars worth of books.

24:45.219 --> 24:51.526
The reward of the Christian who believes and serves Jesus with all their heart and obedience and sacrifice to him.

24:51.827 --> 24:53.949
The reward doesn't come on earth, it comes in heaven.

24:55.051 --> 25:01.939
And it's hard when all the world today tells us, if you do this, you can have riches here and you can do this here.

25:01.979 --> 25:07.506
And we see people who are having the riches here and God says, I don't want that for you.

25:07.650 --> 25:10.073
you to put your trust in me that the reward is after.

25:12.456 --> 25:16.402
It's hard to think about those kind of things because we can't see heaven right now.

25:16.462 --> 25:17.643
We can't feel heaven.

25:17.663 --> 25:21.989
We can't check our account up in heaven to see how much we've got stored up up there.

25:22.049 --> 25:27.957
And it's hard, but Jesus said, listen, if you want treasure on earth, you can have it, but that's all you'll get.

25:30.260 --> 25:31.141
Remember the Pharisees?

25:31.542 --> 25:32.543
Everybody knows this them.

25:32.603 --> 25:33.765
Everybody applauds them.

25:33.825 --> 25:34.866
They have their reward.

25:39.490 --> 25:44.517
If we truly want to sacrifice ourselves, we will truly want to deny ourselves and take up our cross and follow Him.

25:44.938 --> 25:46.380
It's going to take more than what we're doing now.

25:51.868 --> 25:56.976
Because nobody ever obeyed halfway with God and God with what they were reward.

25:59.079 --> 26:00.722
Can't halfway sacrifice an animal.

26:01.603 --> 26:05.128
Can't halfway sacrifice your time and your attention.

26:07.492 --> 26:09.074
Because if you do

26:09.282 --> 26:12.926
If you sacrifice what you want to, when you want to do it, it's wasteful.

26:17.190 --> 26:24.778
When I was in Tennessee, went to a church and people gave stuff to the church, I was like, I'm sacrificing my old cabinet to the church.

26:26.660 --> 26:29.543
Like cabinet wasn't worth the wood it was made out of.

26:29.623 --> 26:31.045
It had been beat up, shot up.

26:31.525 --> 26:32.847
It was that back behind the barn.

26:32.867 --> 26:33.748
They wanted to get rid of it.

26:33.768 --> 26:35.890
They wanted to sacrifice what they wanted to,

26:36.098 --> 26:38.382
when they wanted to do it to make themselves feel better.

26:38.402 --> 26:40.305
Well, listen, that's not what sacrificing is about.

26:42.088 --> 26:47.717
When Jesus went to the cross to be the perfect sacrifice, he wasn't thinking about himself, he was thinking about you and me.

26:50.482 --> 26:57.714
When he sacrificed himself on the cross, he was thinking about how what he was going to do was going to help you and I.

27:03.362 --> 27:06.145
And I guarantee he wasn't thinking about the stories that were going to be made of him.

27:07.487 --> 27:09.329
The movies that he was going to be starred in.

27:10.510 --> 27:11.331
You know what he was thinking about?

27:11.351 --> 27:12.773
He was thinking about you and me.

27:14.755 --> 27:18.059
There's that person in the Bible says that he was not willing that any should perish.

27:20.782 --> 27:22.424
So he made a way we wouldn't have to perish.

27:24.426 --> 27:25.508
He sacrificed himself.

27:27.410 --> 27:31.154
The Bible says that rarely does a good man die for a good person.

27:32.578 --> 27:37.062
But why we were yet sinners Christ died for us.

27:37.082 --> 27:40.065
And he didn't think worried about how much it was going to cost.

27:40.105 --> 27:41.447
He knew it was going to cost everything.

27:43.108 --> 27:49.875
Yet in obedience to the will of God, he went through and because of his sacrifice, you and I have access to God.

27:51.336 --> 27:53.058
You and I have our sins forgiven.

27:57.182 --> 28:01.586
And when it comes to us, Jesus asked us to sacrifice ourselves.

28:03.490 --> 28:06.674
He laid out the model of complete sacrifice so we could see.

28:11.099 --> 28:12.501
The real question is, are we going to follow?

28:14.483 --> 28:18.228
So, well, Pastor, I've always heard that scripture deny yourself, take up your cross and follow me.

28:18.268 --> 28:20.110
That's for people in the ministry.

28:20.771 --> 28:22.693
That was for anybody who would follow Christ.

28:24.095 --> 28:26.177
That was not just for ministers.

28:26.758 --> 28:28.079
That was not just for preachers.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.322
That was for everybody who would follow after you.

28:32.098 --> 28:39.187
all throughout the Bible and throughout the New Testament period, even to the third, fourth, and fifth century, you still find Christians.

28:39.808 --> 28:41.871
In obedience to God, sacrificing themselves.

28:42.612 --> 28:43.653
Doesn't mean they all died.

28:45.315 --> 28:46.697
That means they didn't care if they died.

28:48.499 --> 28:50.141
They didn't care if they lost everything.

28:50.702 --> 28:54.107
They didn't care if tomorrow the world fell apart and they didn't have anything.

28:54.387 --> 28:59.794
As long as they had Jesus and were willing to share Jesus with others, they were doing what they were supposed to do.

29:03.202 --> 29:14.578
Sacrifice is one of the hardest words to swallow in the Bible because it means you can't do what you want to do and be successful.

29:17.883 --> 29:24.672
Sacrifice is only successful when it comes through total and complete obedience to what God asked you to do in the first place.

29:28.017 --> 29:31.762
And what I really want to say is I'm glad Jesus went through with his sacrifice.

29:33.986 --> 29:36.389
because if he hadn't, I don't know where we'd be.

29:38.771 --> 29:41.915
He gave all to show us how to give all.

29:45.259 --> 29:48.643
Thank you for watching today's service, but you really should visit in person.

29:49.524 --> 29:59.475
